I also have to have the money
to pay the marksman.

1209
01:44:32,168 --> 01:44:34,170
Wouldn't that be superfluous,

1210
01:44:34,296 --> 01:44:36,673
considering... that he's dead?

1211
01:44:44,182 --> 01:44:48,061
His aim wasn't quite as good
as you led me to expect.

1212
01:44:48,228 --> 01:44:51,691
The target merely received
a slight flesh wound in the arm.

1213
01:44:51,858 --> 01:44:54,277
Worse than useless.

1214
01:44:54,402 --> 01:44:58,574
Then your French friend panicked,
made a fatal crash,

1215
01:44:58,740 --> 01:45:00,868
landing on the floor of the Albert Hall.

1216
01:45:05,206 --> 01:45:08,001
I don't see how you
can blame me for that.

1217
01:45:08,126 --> 01:45:10,713
He was warmly recommended
by our people in Marrakech.

1218
01:45:10,838 --> 01:45:14,300
I'm glad that you are able
to treat the matter so lightly.

1219
01:45:14,425 --> 01:45:16,761
I'm holding a reception
here this evening.

1220
01:45:16,928 --> 01:45:20,641
In a few moments, I have to welcome
our prime minister as my guest of honour,

1221
01:45:20,766 --> 01:45:24,937
when I hoped and expected
that he would be totally unable to attend.

1222
01:45:26,606 --> 01:45:30,360
- That amuses you, no doubt.
- I don't know what to say...

1223
01:45:30,486 --> 01:45:31,820
No.

1224
01:45:34,740 --> 01:45:38,537
But I do. You have muddled everything
from the start.

1225
01:45:38,662 --> 01:45:41,165
Taking that child
with you from Marrakech.

1226
01:45:41,290 --> 01:45:44,752
Don't you realise that Americans
dislike having their children stolen?

1227
01:45:44,877 --> 01:45:47,922
How else could I make sure
that McKenna would keep quiet?

1228
01:45:48,089 --> 01:45:51,218
Then, to crown it all, you get cold feet

1229
01:45:51,343 --> 01:45:55,306
and come running along here to hide,
bringing the wretched child with you.

1230
01:45:55,431 --> 01:45:58,852
Don't you see what you've done
to the diplomatic status of this embassy?

1231
01:45:58,977 --> 01:46:01,063
I didn't think.
I only thought we could -

1232
01:46:01,188 --> 01:46:05,943
How are you going to get
the child out of here, eh? Eh? EH?

1233
01:46:06,819 --> 01:46:09,197
No difficulty about that, surely?
The car.

1234
01:46:09,322 --> 01:46:13,911
With plainclothes detectives planted
right 'round this building?

1235
01:46:14,036 --> 01:46:16,873
You English intellectuals
will be the death of us all.

1236
01:46:16,998 --> 01:46:19,000
I'll think of something.
Only give me time.

1237
01:46:19,167 --> 01:46:21,127
Time. Huh!

1238
01:46:28,511 --> 01:46:31,932
I want the child
removed from this embassy,

1239
01:46:32,057 --> 01:46:36,437
and removed in such a way
that he won't be able to say any more

1240
01:46:36,562 --> 01:46:38,564
where he has been tonight.

1241
01:46:38,689 --> 01:46:40,191
Oh, no!

1242
01:46:44,279 --> 01:46:47,283
- I'll see to it.
- Drayton!

1243
01:46:47,783 --> 01:46:50,328
I trust that nothing
will go wrong this time.

1244
01:46:56,794 --> 01:46:58,963
It would be very unfortunate for you if -

1245
01:47:00,882 --> 01:47:02,676
Yes, come in.

1246
01:47:05,429 --> 01:47:09,267
Your Excellency, the princess should be
arriving at any moment.

1247
01:47:21,906 --> 01:47:24,200
I recognised him. He recognised me.

1248
01:47:24,367 --> 01:47:27,246
He tried to get away, made a jump for it.
That was all.

1249
01:47:27,413 --> 01:47:29,915
Trying to liquidate
one of their own big shots.

1250
01:47:30,082 --> 01:47:32,919
I wish they'd stick to their usual custom
and do it in their own country.

1251
01:47:36,089 --> 01:47:38,050
Yes?

1252
01:47:39,760 --> 01:47:41,721
Buchanan speaking.

1253
01:47:45,183 --> 01:47:47,185
Right. Thank you.

1254
01:47:48,187 --> 01:47:50,189
The Draytons are at the embassy.

1255
01:47:50,314 --> 01:47:52,316
- The what?
- How do you know?

1256
01:47:52,441 --> 01:47:55,070
We have ways of finding out,
from the inside.

1257
01:47:55,236 --> 01:47:58,407
If the Draytons are at the embassy,
then our boy's there too.

1258
01:47:58,532 --> 01:48:02,745
- Probably. But we can't do anything.
- What do you mean?

1259
01:48:02,870 --> 01:48:05,498
Every embassy in a foreign country
has extra-territorial rights.

1260
01:48:05,623 --> 01:48:08,919
- What's that? - It's as if
the embassy is on foreign soil.

1261
01:48:09,044 --> 01:48:12,590
So they can steal kids
and get away with it? What is this!

1262
01:48:12,715 --> 01:48:16,428
We could have the Foreign Office serve
a writ on the ambassador.

1263
01:48:16,553 --> 01:48:20,098
I'm not responsible for the complications
of international law.

1264
01:48:20,265 --> 01:48:24,687
If only we had some positive proof
that your boy really is in there.

1265
01:48:31,361 --> 01:48:34,156
Say, wh-what's the phone number
of that embassy?

1266
01:48:34,323 --> 01:48:36,701
- You got it?
- What are you thinking of -

1267
01:48:36,826 --> 01:48:40,288
- Let me try something.
- Grosvenor 0-1-4-4.

1268
01:48:40,455 --> 01:48:43,125
Grosvenor 0-1-4-4, please.

1269
01:48:44,043 --> 01:48:46,629
That fellow that got shot's
a prime minister, isn't he?

1270
01:48:48,673 --> 01:48:52,136
Hello? Hello, I'd like to speak to
the prime minister, please.

1271
01:48:52,261 --> 01:48:54,430
Yeah, yeah. No, look...

1272
01:48:54,555 --> 01:48:57,308
Just tell him the lady that saved his life
would like to speak to him.

1273
01:48:57,433 --> 01:49:00,896
- It's very important.
- Ben, what do I say?

1274
01:49:01,021 --> 01:49:03,148
He wanted to visit with us
so he could thank you.

1275
01:49:03,273 --> 01:49:05,693
Tell him you want to come over
to the embassy tonight,

1276
01:49:05,818 --> 01:49:08,196
cos we're going to leave London
tomorrow.

1277
01:49:08,363 --> 01:49:10,282
Hello? Here you are.

1278
01:49:10,407 --> 01:49:11,908
Hello?

1279
01:49:12,034 --> 01:49:15,871
My dear lady, this is a charming surprise.

1280
01:49:16,872 --> 01:49:18,833
Uh-huh.

1281
01:49:19,834 --> 01:49:23,338
Mm-hm. Delighted. Delighted, delighted.

1282
01:49:23,505 --> 01:49:26,091
The ambassador too would be delighted.

1283
01:49:26,217 --> 01:49:28,594
Any friends of mine are friends of his.

1284
01:49:32,474 --> 01:49:34,309
He said all right.

1285
01:49:35,018 --> 01:49:37,980
- If he asks you, we're all set.
- What if they don't?

1286
01:49:38,147 --> 01:49:40,817
Have we ever been to a party
where they didn't ask you?

1287
01:49:40,942 --> 01:49:43,862
Now, your job is to hold
their attention, right?

1288
01:49:48,784 --> 01:49:51,371
Good evening -
Dr and Mrs McKenna.

1289
01:49:51,538 --> 01:49:53,999
How very nice to see you.

1290
01:49:54,124 --> 01:49:57,127
The prime minister's waiting for you.
Come this way.

1291
01:50:05,470 --> 01:50:07,306
Ah, madam!

1292
01:50:08,098 --> 01:50:11,769
- Good evening, good evening.
- Good evening.

1293
01:50:11,936 --> 01:50:15,482
This is the charming lady
who saved my life at the concert.

1294
01:50:15,607 --> 01:50:20,738
Madam, you saved the life of the one man
who's irreplaceable in our country.

1295
01:50:22,490 --> 01:50:25,410
I hear you are the famous Jo Conway,
madam?

1296
01:50:25,535 --> 01:50:28,831
- Yes, I'm Jo Conway.
- Perhaps we might...

1297
01:50:28,956 --> 01:50:31,751
I'm sure my wife would be delighted
to sing for you.

1298
01:50:31,876 --> 01:50:35,088
- Wouldn't you, dear?
- Well, it's been quite some time...

1299
01:50:35,213 --> 01:50:36,506
I beg you, madam.

1300
01:50:36,631 --> 01:50:40,469
A tranquil coda
to conclude a dramatic evening.

1301
01:50:40,636 --> 01:50:41,888
I'm very flattered.

1302
01:50:42,013 --> 01:50:44,140
Um, Stanis?

1303
01:50:45,100 --> 01:50:47,769
Would you put up some chairs?
And hurry up, please.

1304
01:50:47,894 --> 01:50:53,735
Ladies and gentlemen, Jo Conway has
consented to sing a few songs for us.

1305
01:50:54,736 --> 01:50:58,323
Darling, would you see
that the prime minister gets a good seat.

1306
01:50:59,700 --> 01:51:03,955
Would you like to come to the piano?
I do hope it's tuned.

1307
01:51:04,080 --> 01:51:07,292
- Would you not like to sit down, sir?
- Er...

1308
01:51:07,459 --> 01:51:10,129
No, thank you. I'll just stand over here.

