# When I was just a little girl

1310
01:51:29,609 --> 01:51:34,115
# I asked my mother, What will I be?

1311
01:51:34,240 --> 01:51:38,912
# Will I be pretty? Will I be rich?

1312
01:51:39,037 --> 01:51:43,250
# Here's what she said to me

1313
01:51:43,375 --> 01:51:47,881
# Que sera, sera

1314
01:51:48,047 --> 01:51:51,843
# Whatever will be, will be

1315
01:51:52,678 --> 01:51:56,015
# The future's not ours to see

1316
01:51:56,474 --> 01:52:00,228
# Que sera, sera

1317
01:52:00,395 --> 01:52:05,317
# What will be, will be

1318
01:52:05,484 --> 01:52:09,113
# When I was just a child in school

1319
01:52:09,239 --> 01:52:12,492
# I asked my teacher, What should I try?

1320
01:52:13,577 --> 01:52:17,665
# Should I paint pictures?
Should I sing songs?

1321
01:52:17,790 --> 01:52:21,169
# This was her wise reply

1322
01:52:21,294 --> 01:52:25,549
# Que sera, sera

1323
01:52:25,674 --> 01:52:29,887
# Whatever will be, will be

1324
01:52:30,013 --> 01:52:33,433
# The future's not ours to see

1325
01:52:43,612 --> 01:52:46,573
# When I grew up and fell in love

1326
01:52:46,699 --> 01:52:52,414
# I asked my sweetheart,
What lies ahead?

1327
01:52:52,539 --> 01:52:57,544
# Will we have rainbows day after day

1328
01:52:57,670 --> 01:53:01,132
# Here's what my sweetheart said

1329
01:53:01,257 --> 01:53:05,387
# Que sera, sera

1330
01:53:05,512 --> 01:53:09,976
# Whatever will be, will be

1331
01:53:10,101 --> 01:53:14,564
# The future's not ours to see...

1332
01:53:14,731 --> 01:53:16,733
That's my mother's voice!

1333
01:53:16,858 --> 01:53:20,571
- That's my mother singing!
- What?

1334
01:53:22,198 --> 01:53:24,242
Are you sure, Hank?

1335
01:53:24,367 --> 01:53:26,369
Are you quite sure?

1336
01:53:26,495 --> 01:53:28,330
That's her! I know it!

1337
01:53:30,833 --> 01:53:32,794
What's she doing here?

1338
01:53:47,185 --> 01:53:50,147
Hank, can you whistle that song?

1339
01:53:50,272 --> 01:53:52,316
I guess so.

1340
01:53:54,652 --> 01:53:56,613
Then go on. Whistle it.

1341
01:53:56,780 --> 01:53:59,283
Whistle it as loud as you can.

1342
01:54:10,128 --> 01:54:12,715
# Will we have rainbows

1343
01:54:12,882 --> 01:54:15,259
# Day after day?

1344
01:54:15,385 --> 01:54:18,805
# Here's what my sweetheart said

1345
01:54:23,936 --> 01:54:27,899
# Ever will be, will be

1346
01:54:28,066 --> 01:54:31,361
# The future's not ours to see

1347
01:54:31,528 --> 01:54:33,989
# Que sera, sera

1348
01:54:35,116 --> 01:54:38,995
# What will be, will be

1349
01:54:39,120 --> 01:54:42,249
# Now I have children of my own

1350
01:54:42,416 --> 01:54:47,255
# They ask their mother, What will I be?

1351
01:54:47,422 --> 01:54:52,886
# Will I be handsome? Will I be rich?

1352
01:54:53,053 --> 01:54:58,226
# I tell them tenderly

1353
01:54:58,351 --> 01:55:02,814
# Que sera, sera

1354
01:55:02,940 --> 01:55:07,236
# Whatever will be, will be

1355
01:55:07,361 --> 01:55:10,824
# The future's not ours to see

1356
01:55:10,949 --> 01:55:15,204
# Que sera, sera

1357
01:55:15,329 --> 01:55:19,834
# What will be, will be... #

1358
01:55:19,959 --> 01:55:23,505
You two wait in the mail room.
I'll bring him down.

1359
01:55:25,799 --> 01:55:28,135
Give me about five minutes.

1360
01:56:25,869 --> 01:56:27,162
No!

1361
01:56:30,207 --> 01:56:32,251
Oh, Daddy!

1362
01:56:34,295 --> 01:56:36,464
Take the boy. Go! But you must be quick!

1363
01:56:36,590 --> 01:56:38,592
Come on, son.

1364
01:56:43,055 --> 01:56:44,474
Don't touch him.

1365
01:56:49,646 --> 01:56:51,690
I don't think
you're going to do any shooting,

1366
01:56:51,857 --> 01:56:54,444
not with these people
downstairs and police outside.

1367
01:56:54,569 --> 01:56:57,989
You're not in a very happy
position yourself, you know.

1368
01:56:59,574 --> 01:57:03,704
- You've got to let the boy go!
- Precisely what I'm thinking.

1369
01:57:04,205 --> 01:57:08,460
Now I'm sure you're going to be sensible
and help me out of here.

1370
01:57:08,585 --> 01:57:11,422
Don't ask me for help, you miserable s-

1371
01:57:11,588 --> 01:57:14,800
You wouldn't want
your father to get hurt, would you, Hank?

1372
01:57:17,095 --> 01:57:20,557
Now we're going
to walk downstairs together, casually,

1373
01:57:20,724 --> 01:57:22,893
like three old friends.

1374
01:57:23,018 --> 01:57:27,231
Then we're going to take a stroll
as far as the nearest taxi rank.

1375
01:57:27,398 --> 01:57:30,861
I hope there won't be
any emotional scenes on the way down.

1376
01:57:31,028 --> 01:57:33,030
Do as he says, Hank.

1377
01:57:35,116 --> 01:57:37,660
No, the other way. The other way.

1378
01:57:37,785 --> 01:57:39,788
Shall we be going?

1379
01:57:39,955 --> 01:57:41,915
All right, start down the hall, son.

1380
01:57:44,543 --> 01:57:46,546
Don't say anything.

1381
01:58:21,377 --> 01:58:26,258
# Now it's goodbye

1382
01:58:26,383 --> 01:58:28,552
# And we're facing

1383
01:58:28,678 --> 01:58:34,685
# Such lonely tomorrows

1384
01:58:36,019 --> 01:58:40,149
# So many sunsets

1385
01:58:40,316 --> 01:58:43,695
# Till there's a sunset

1386
01:58:44,780 --> 01:58:47,533
# When all at once

1387
01:58:47,700 --> 01:58:51,329
# You'll be there

1388
01:58:52,705 --> 01:58:56,793
# Then we'll

1389
01:58:56,919 --> 01:59:00,256
# Kiss again

1390
01:59:00,381 --> 01:59:04,052
# And again

1391
01:59:04,219 --> 01:59:05,971
# And again #

1392
01:59:15,482 --> 01:59:17,484
Hank!

1393
01:59:20,863 --> 01:59:22,824
Come on, Hank.

1394
01:59:29,081 --> 01:59:31,083
Oh, Mother!

1395
01:59:38,300 --> 01:59:41,804
I'm sorry we were gone so long,
but we go and pick up Hank.

1396
01:59:41,929 --> 01:59:43,931
Ohh!

